The paper presents a neural operator for Bayesian inference, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. The use of ODE-based neural operators and meta-learning frameworks suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with sequential inference, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper presents examples involving high-dimensional data, which is a common theme in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
